Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.35,0:00:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My name's Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Duelist aimin' for Duel Champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We have to get back the pieces of my memories that have been scattered, the Numbers cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can it, will you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.48,0:00:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something big's happening in my city right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.61,0:00:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A computer virus bomb's about to spread!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it activates, the city'll be thrown into a huge panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.49,0:00:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the culprit's my highly respected teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.49,0:00:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta beat him in a Duel to stop the virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.41,0:00:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'im!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.50,0:00:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face-down and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.01,0:00:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.39,0:00:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he used my Monster that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}20 minutes remain until virus bomb is released.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}my{\i0} turn, pal!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just me, or has Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} been talking to himself this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.03,0:00:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, is he okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.90,0:00:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, it's fine. Don't pay him any mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.70,0:01:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just Yuma's "Bring it to 'em" mode...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, go Summon Ganbara Knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't butt into someone else's problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.33,0:01:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Numbers is riding on this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.25,0:01:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we do not get his Numbers, I will be obliterated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I give a care about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't strong enough to win on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.31,0:01:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.39,0:01:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's your reason, then that's the final straw!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't do a single thing you tell me to do during this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.77,0:01:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by not doing anything I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.44,0:01:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means if you tell me to move my right hand, I'll just move my left!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.07,0:01:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you tell me to play Ganbara Knight...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.57,0:01:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll Summon Achacha Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.83,0:01:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.91,0:01:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is successfully Summoned, my opponent takes 500 points of damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothin' to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just gave Sensei some damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.22,0:02:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it came with a high price.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had you Summoned Ganbara Knight, you would have had two Level Four Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.19,0:02:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have Exceed Summoned Aspiring Emperor - Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! I messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that already!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How {\i1}dare you{\i0} damage my Life...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.49,0:02:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.58,0:02:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damage Vaccine OmegaÎ© MAX!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I take damage, this card recovers\N my Life by the damage I received!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,*Shock*
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my attack just now was wasted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I yearn for a perfect victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.97,0:02:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you injure even a speck of my Life!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I try to say I was being used, the fact remains that I was the one who launched the virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, I'll be blamed as the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're running out of time, Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.65,0:03:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.82,0:03:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.23,0:03:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.01,0:03:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.41,0:03:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.62,0:03:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.42,0:03:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:04:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.17,0:04:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.24,0:04:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.31,0:04:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.39,0:04:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(542,491)}"Numbers 4: The Countdown to Reversal!\N The Ace-In-The-Hole's Astral!?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be a switch for the virus bomb in here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.14,0:04:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm gonna stop the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end my turn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Numbers 34 - Computer Beast Terabyte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can remove one of its Overlay Units once per turn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gain control over one of my\N opponent's Level Four or lower Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AHH! He snatched my Gogogo Golem again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.37,0:05:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had Summoned Hope, he wouldn't have been able to steal him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The effect Terabyte holds only allows it to control Monsters with units of level.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Exceed Monsters don't have actual levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Dueling is defective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should just obey me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take damage, but Gogogo Golem's gonna return to my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it does...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so foolish a Duelist that I'd use the exact same strategy I used in my previous turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Continuous Magics, Virus Mail and Cracking!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.79,0:05:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's a Continuous Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Normal Magic Cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuous Magics will continue their effects as long as the card remains on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The effect of Virus Mail lets me select a Level Four or lower Monster and Direct Attack with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And afterwards, the Monster is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the battle, Gogogo Golem will be destroyed by Virus Mail's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, I activate the effects of my other Continuous Magic, Cracking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.25,0:06:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When your Monster is destroyed and sent to the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you receive 800 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.09,0:06:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.85,0:06:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my Terabyte Combo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:06:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Terabyte Combo's gonna bring me some problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your body's starting to fade a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as your Life is injured, my own life is obliterated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your... life...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.54,0:07:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you fail, you will lose something of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with Yuma all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems kinda down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh, gotta do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.67,0:07:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.93,0:07:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a {\i1}Garyouhousuu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}[Literally "Unrecognized Genius", but also can literally mean "Crouching Dragon, Young Phoenix"]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.64,0:07:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}Gachouhoso{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.64,0:07:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8} [Literally "Weak Goose"]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Garyou{\i0} as in a crouching dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}housuu{\i0} refers to a Houou - a young Phoenix!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.15,0:07:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, outstanding talent lies dormant within you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you unlock that talent, you will no doubt win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're praising me too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sweet! Lem'me do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.79,0:08:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number six...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humans work their hardest when they are praised."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, truthfully, I need to speak with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.55,0:08:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You possess an eternal combo of recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jump aimlessly over boxes and you drown yourself in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You change your character at whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you are intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ya jerk! You looking for a fight!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.57,0:08:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The elevator...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.91,0:08:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.33,0:08:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can see the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're moving upwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.63,0:08:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.68,0:08:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the final door!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.77,0:09:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mock the Karate Glove!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.74,0:09:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be your front row seats \Nto the view of my virus bomb's success!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.75,0:09:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face-down and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot! What's wrong with Sensei?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma is going to lose to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I must win at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't do a single thing you tell me to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It means if you tell me to move my right hand, I'll just move my left!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got that approach too...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.23,0:09:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:09:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got me a sweet card!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:10:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Goblindbergh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! When Goblindbergh is Summoned successfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.54,0:10:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in summary, he can Special Summon a Level Four or lower Monster from his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, use Zubaba Knight from your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.46,0:10:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heck no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.63,0:10:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you told me to play Zubaba Knight...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll go an' Special Summon Ganbara Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got the Level Four Ganbara Knight and Goblindbergh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.48,0:10:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.31,0:10:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can go an' Exceed Summon Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Four Ganbara Knight and Goblindbergh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.04,0:10:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I construct the Overlay Network with these two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.87,0:10:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exceed Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.42,0:10:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Numbers 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.71,0:10:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's up to you, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.36,0:11:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 39.. Aspiring Emperor, Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.62,0:11:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma. Don't set down the trap card from your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one you cannot use.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Listen up, I'm not gonna follow your orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.88,0:11:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card from my hand, turn end !!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.28,0:11:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time that you gave back my manuscript!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.58,0:11:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.45,0:11:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.64,0:11:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.06,0:11:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terabyte's effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.39,0:11:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use an Overlay Unit to gain control of Achacha Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Took my Monster again...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, with the effect of the Continuous Magic, Virus Mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Achacha Archer will be destroyed after attacking you directly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.24,0:12:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this continues, in summary, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} will lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there something I can do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.29,0:12:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't Hope have a great effect of his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.76,0:12:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.30,0:12:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Hope's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.47,0:12:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use an Overlay Unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can then negate a Monster's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Virus Mail has the effect to automatically destroy the Monster when it successfully attacks you directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By negating it using Hope's effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.16,0:12:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will not go into the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And moreover, Cracking's effect won't activate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! So Sensei's combo was blocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? And here I thought you were dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.46,0:13:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} seems much smarter than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.76,0:13:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, it's because of the Dueling Spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dueling Spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.59,0:13:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now he can't use his Overlay Units anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! He can't use his Terabyte Combo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do hope you didn't think I hadn't read right through your little strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.60,0:13:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The conditions for my perfect victory have been set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.61,0:13:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.74,0:13:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bug Switch!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Bugman X, Y and Z are in my Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can switch my Defense Position Monster into Attack Mode
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to Special Summon Super Bugman in Face-Up Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it'd be in Attack Mode, but the Monster's in Defense Mode...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.59,0:13:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really thought I'd do something so pointless?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Super Bugman's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is in Face-Up Defense Mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.77,0:13:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can switch the Attack Points of all Attack Position Monsters with their Defense Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.73,0:14:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terabyte holds 2900 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, Terabyte's Attack Power becomes 2900!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.57,0:14:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2900 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, Hope's and Archer's Attack Power...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.03,0:14:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then proceed to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.37,0:14:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Terabyte!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.96,0:14:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.46,0:14:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.67,0:14:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duh! Of course I'll dodge it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.17,0:14:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Hope's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.67,0:14:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use an Overlay Unit to negate a Monster's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just used all of Hope's Overlay Units!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.93,0:14:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} can't block any more attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card in reverse, ending my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His set card...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.57,0:14:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear that the next turn will bring this match to a close!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.29,0:15:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terabyte's got 2900 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't beat Sensei this turn, Hope's a goner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.83,0:15:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me give you a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may be wrong, but I think using Zubaba Knight and Achacha Archer to Exceed Summon Revise Dragon would be a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.55,0:15:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah! I have another Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Zubaba Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Three Zubaba Knight and Achacha Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I construct the Overlay Network with these two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exceed Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Numbers 17!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.75,0:15:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revise Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.01,0:15:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A second Numbers, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you seem to have forgotten about Super Bugman's effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.72,0:15:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Super Bugman remains on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.97,0:16:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Attack Power and Defense Power of all Attack Position Monsters on the field are switched.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revise Dragon's Defense Power is zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So its Attack Power is now zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.69,0:16:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went through the trouble of Summoning Revise Dragon, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you had to go and open your big mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just had to go and butt in before!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't told me to dodge before...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No way this guy would tell me to do something so stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.50,0:16:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It means if you tell me to move my right hand, I'll just move my left!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't mean you...! On purpose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, activate Thunder Shot from your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, your victory is set.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.34,0:16:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do not, I will be obliterated from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Thunder Shot Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card damages my opponent by 500 points for each Monster they control on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's 1000 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What useless struggling!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will once again activate Damage Vaccine OmegaÎ© MAX!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.25,0:17:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card recovers my Life by the amount of damage I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.71,0:17:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was totally pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, use your Trap Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.72,0:17:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Trap Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.76,0:17:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Trap Card, Excessive Insecurity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my opponent recovers his Life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the Monsters my opponent controls is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.73,0:17:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll be destroying Super Bugman!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.03,0:17:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smart! So that means, in summary, Super Bugman's effect disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.45,0:17:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Monsters whose Attack and Defense were switched are returned to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.29,0:17:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terabyte has zero Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Revise Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.80,0:17:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Terabyte!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I Direct Attack with Aspiring Hero - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Slash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.49,0:18:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did it! Yuma won!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a brilliant victorious turnaround!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won, WON!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.41,0:18:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I BROUGHT IT TO 'IM!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.88,0:18:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You managed to win somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.71,0:18:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how'd you know Sensei was gonna try to recover his Life?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.59,0:18:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he was seeking perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.97,0:18:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was naturally playing his Dueling at the utmost perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to bet on the high chance that he would try to recover the damage he lost from Thunder Shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is another of the cards holding my scattered memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers 34...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.21,0:19:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the place I come from...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is the Astral World.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.98,0:19:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I came to this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei! Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.31,0:19:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.65,0:19:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What was I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, you have to hurry up and stop the virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Virus bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. I can't stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.08,0:19:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the deactivation switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the city...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're way too persistent!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.38,0:20:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The timer didn't stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}3...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.84,0:20:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}2...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.22,0:20:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}1...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The city's about to go into a huge panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.69,0:20:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this about a "huge panic"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sensei, didn't you hack the city's computers to try and plunge the city into a state of mass panic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.40,0:20:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I do something so terrifying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.86,0:20:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I confess to causing a bit of trouble for the city while making preparations...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.33,0:20:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't making a virus bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, it's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.29,0:20:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.88,0:20:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids, try looking into the sky with your D-Gazers on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the sky with our D-Gazers on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.80,0:20:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Bugman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A GIANT BUGMAN!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.52,0:20:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to realize.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coincidently, the night view in this city happens to make up the matrix code.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.11,0:21:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it responds with our D-Gazers and materializes Bugman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the code was incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.24,0:21:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the light in that building down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the perfection you were talking about was putting light on that building?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei~
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.97,0:21:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... the Bugman card?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Read it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Bugman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cute~!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.43,0:21:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bugman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't make it in time, but nothing happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bugman...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An electrical fairy that lives off of the other bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It becomes extremely powerful because it lives off its bug friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that those who witness its full moon-like appearance may forever live in happiness."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.79,0:22:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, Sensei just wanted all of us to live forever in happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number seven...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.00,0:22:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"My memory pieces, the Numbers cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They grow the desire and darkness that dwells inside those they come into contact with."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.06,0:22:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be sure to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.36,0:22:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's this week's question!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.82,0:22:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Monster is placed in Attack Mode, it's in an offensive stance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.20,0:22:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how about when it's in Defense Mode?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.35,0:22:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanna watch TV when I get home.\N The recent anime are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.07,0:23:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, this test is hard. \NLanguage, Math and English are especially bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm only average at science and social studies.\N The only thing I'm good at is P.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.75,0:23:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Wait up, Baby!) For who's sake...
